        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 4 at 4:02AM EDT by NWS Jacksonville FL</headline>
        <description>At 402 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Country Club Estates, or over Dock Junction, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts around 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
St Simons Island Village, Brunswick, Country Club Estates, St. Simons
Island, Dock Junction, Sea Island, Boys Estate, Dover Bluff, and
Jekyll Island.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
